The paper deals with algorithms for hypergraph two-coloring, which is a problem in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. The focus is on the streaming model, which is a subfield of algorithms and data structures. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves probabilistic analysis and information theory, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with hypergraph theory, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
